John Wayne Conlee (born August 11, 1946) is an American country music singer.
Conlee was born on a tobacco farm in Versailles, Kentucky.
By 1971, he moved to Nashville, Tennessee, in pursuit of a musical career, signing to ABC Records in 1976.
In 2005, Conlee donated his performance of "Rose Colored Glasses" at a concert at the Wildhorse Saloon in Nashville to benefit the Lymphatic Research Foundation (New York).
